{
  "stem": "3100.1",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.9,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And I think that some of the SS had created this little camp to-- to be able to say that they are employed, that they have a camp, not to take them to the front of whatever it is.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They took us to Budzyn right after this.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we know that there is no more Jewish people and they're free.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In the meanwhile, while they took us-- while we were at this camp in park near the railroad station, I found out that my elder brother, Sholom, which married in the beginning of the war, and he lived in a little town, [INAUDIBLE], which was also in the Lublin District.",
      "word_count": 50
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That it happened there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "That they took out all the Jews there, and he ran away from there by foot, and he came into Krasnik.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he find out from whoever he asked that I was interrogated in this park.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was able to get him in.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And then I was with my brother together.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Then after a while, they took us out all from there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And they took us by foot, which was 6 kilometers away to Budzyn camp.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And in Budzyn, I was there until the end of '43, till about-- what, for about two years.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The camp was called a labor camp not a concentration camps in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Then we had our daily portion of a little-- a little piece of bread, and soup, and so-called coffee, which was only [NON-ENGLISH], it was black.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we had to live in it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And we had to work.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "They created there a [GERMAN] that they-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they worked out there were two camps.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "One in one side and one across the street, which the Poles helped have builded up an ammunition [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
